# Component Structure

Every new component must live in its own directory under `app/components/`.

## Required layout

```
app/components/ComponentName/
  index.tsx       # component implementation (default export)
  README.md       # usage docs with import example
  index.test.tsx  # unit tests
```

## Rules

- Name the directory in PascalCase matching the component (e.g. `TopNav/`).
- Put the component in `index.tsx`, not `ComponentName.tsx`.
- Import via the directory path: `import TopNav from "@/app/components/TopNav"`.
- Add a `README.md` with purpose, usage example, and how to run tests.
- Add `index.test.tsx` covering key render and interaction behavior.
- Run tests with `npm run test:run` (or `npm test` in watch mode).
- Keep Headless UI and other client-only APIs in `index.tsx` behind `'use client'` when needed.

## Example

```
app/components/TopNav/
  index.tsx
  README.md
  index.test.tsx
```
